verse.lines:
I am stepping across the invisible line from time to eternity;
I am fully expecting the next breath I take
To be in the place He's prepared for me;
I'm living my life on the verge of the rapture,
Knowing in what I believe;
It's so close I can feel it, so near I can see it,
I am ready for the stepping across.

Oh what beauty waits for the Bride over yonder,
Such a joy and a peace that our minds cannot comprehend;
Oh how I anticipate eternity with my Savior,
Blessed communion with Jesus that will have no end;
No more pain or death, no more find of rest,
Only love, only joy, only peace, only Jesus I see.
